  "text": "Under the optimized conditions, the CTL intensity is proportional to the concentration of acetophenone and exhibits a linear range of 15-280 mg/m 3 (2.8-52 ppm), and a detection limit of 4 mg/m 3 (0.7 ppm) is obtained at S/N = 3. The linear regression equation is Y = 100.9 X -1356 (correlation coefficient R 2 = 0.9968), where Y is the relative CTL intensity, X is the concentration of acetophenone (Figure 6b ). Compared to the previously reported sensors for acetophenone [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the present sensor shows wider linear range and lower LOD. The detail can be seen in Table 1 . ",
